text.text:
PROTECT THE BEAUTY AND FUNCTIONALITY OF YOUR SYSTEM

by enrolling into a McKay Landscape Lighting maintenance program

Regular maintenance will help keep your landscape lighting system performing and looking its best year after year. When you enroll in one of our maintenance programs, you'll enjoy the peace of mind knowing your outdoor lighting system is working as it was first intended.

params.html:
LANDSCAPE LIGHTING MAINTENANCE PROGRAMS

FIND THE BEST PROGRAM FOR YOUR LIGHTING NEEDS

To protect your investment, we offer annual, bi-annual, and quarterly maintenance programs including a hassle-free automatic renewal option, so you wonâ€™t have to worry about requesting service with us each year. The following is a guide to help you determine the best program for your property and needs. Please feel free to contact us to learn more or if you need help selecting a program.

ESSENTIAL PACKAGE:
Annual Service

Recommended for properties with less than 50 fixtures. Once a year we'll visit your property to perform service. 

You pay an hourly service fee, the cost of all bulbs, and any repairs.

{{cta('5b4831b2-aa1a-497f-b511-b3dedc5453ff')}}

GOLD PACKAGE:
Bi-Annual Service

Recommended for properties with approximately 50-100 fixtures. Twice a year we'll visit your property to perform service. 

You pay a flat rate service fee per visit and FREE bulb replacement during the second visit.

{{cta('d6a29609-527d-41fd-abd3-dcc5b5151667')}}

PLATINUM PACKAGE:
Quarterly Service

Recommended for properties with more than 100 fixtures. Once a quarter we'll visit your property to perform service. 

You pay a flat rate service fee per visit and FREE bulb replacement during the second, third, and fourth visit

{{cta('f4e32ae9-5737-4260-8de2-c38aad0e3cc8')}}

params.html:
WHAT'S INCLUDED

Save time, money, and more importantly, peace of mind

Enrolling in one of our maintenance service programs will not only save you time but also money. Otherwise, you'll incur a service call fee, plus of the cost of bulbs for each visit and we can not guarantee the bulbs. When you join one of our maintenance programs, an experienced service technician performs the following:

Bulb Replacement

Over the life of a bulb, its brightness tends to diminish. Burned out bulbs or using the wrong bulb can negatively impact your system. We replace ALL of halogen bulbs OR inspect and only replace faulty LED bulbs.

Realign Fixtures

Ever-growing tree and plant roots underneath the surface can push fixtures upwards. We make sure your fixtures are properly aligned and situated into the ground, lighting what's important.

Clean Fixtures & Lenses

Dirt, debris, and mineral deposits can build up and make your lights appear dimmer than normal. We thoroughly clean your fixtures and lenses.

Inspect Photocells & Transformers

We'll inspect and make certain no little critters are preventing your photocells or transformers from properly working.

Check & Reset Timers

Some timers can lose time, need adjusting as the season's change, or battery replacement. We'll assure your timer is properly functioning and turning on and off at the correct times.

System Performance Checks

We also run through performance checks to affirm your system is performing and working its best.

Complete Any Necessary Repairs

If any preventative repairs are needed, we'll complete them to help prevent any major problems from occurring in the future.

Our maintenance programs are designed to help ensure the longevity, functionality, and reliability of your lighting system. And if we installed your system, all of your information is stored in our database. Our team will be aware of any past repairs that have been performed or any pending service thatâ€™s needed. 

 

 

You always have the McKay 100% Satisfaction Guarantee. 

When you enroll in one of our service programs, each bulb is then guaranteed for the one-year contract period. If they fail, you can give us a call and we'll promptly take care of it. 

Any additional service request visits for timer resets, electrical issues, and system repairs or modifications are not covered under the Maintenance Service Programs.
